description:
&lt;p&gt;30 Hours Term Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within Shropshire Community Health Trust to appoint an enthusiastic Public Health Nursing Service Screener to join the School Nursing Team in Shropshire based in the central team in Shrewsbury. The team provides school nursing services to children and young people within the county of Shropshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our award winning, innovative and dynamic school nurse team support health and wellbeing programmes for all children and young people aged 5-19 in schools and the wider community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated individuals with experience of working with children, young people and families. You should have the ability to work within a skill mixed team, under the delegation of the school nurse to deliver allocated components of the Healthy Child Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be to provide the NCMP screening to school aged children at year reception and year 6. The post holder will assist the public health nursing team to deliver the Healthy Child Programme and be involved in maximising the health of children, families and the community.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake some administrative duties to support the team, including the inputting of clinical data and maintaining accurate school health records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;AS A MANDATORY PART OF THE RECRUITMENT PROCESS YOU SHOULD ANSWER THE FOLLOWING QUESTION IN YOUR SUPPORTING STATEMENT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;(MINIMUM OF 200 WORDS):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is your understanding of the National Childhood Programme, and why is it important to screen children?  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
